N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 19 ยง 332.7 - Voter who has not previously filed

State Regulations
A military voter who has not previously filed an
application on or before October 21, 1976 or having filed an application has
not received a military ballot, may sign such an application and personally
file the same with the board of elections of the county of his residence on or
before noon of November 2, 1976. Upon such filing his name shall be entered in
the register of voters or on the registration records. Notes
